sequenceDiagram
    participant Operator as TrustyAI Operator<br/>(LMEvalJob Controller)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant JobPod as LMEval Job Pod<br/>(lm-evaluation-harness)
    participant EvalHub as EvalHub Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HFHub as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Model as Model Serving Endpoint<br/>8080/TCP or 443/TCP
    participant Registry as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Operator,Registry: Flow 1: LMEval Batch Evaluation Job

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Step 1: Create K8s Job<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>JobPod: Pod scheduled & started

    JobPod->>JobPod: Step 2: Read job spec<br/>from ConfigMap mount<br/>/meta/job.json

    JobPod->>EvalHub: Step 3: Report initialization status<br/>POST callback_url<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+

    JobPod->>HFHub: Step 4: Download tokenizers/datasets<br/>GET HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: HF Token (optional)
    HFHub-->>JobPod: Tokenizer & dataset artifacts

    loop For each evaluation batch
        JobPod->>Model: Step 5: POST /v1/completions<br/>HTTP(S)/8080 or 443<br/>Auth: None/Bearer Token
        Model-->>JobPod: Completion responses
    end

    Note over JobPod: Compute evaluation metrics

    JobPod->>Registry: Step 6: Push OCI artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Basic Auth/Docker config
    Registry-->>JobPod: Push confirmed

    JobPod->>EvalHub: Step 7: Report final results<br/>POST callback_url<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+

    Note over JobPod: Job completes (exit 0)
